Partly cloudy- near calm- only 0.5" of rain since last secchi reading on August 20.
Partly cloudy- northwest wind at about 5 mph- about 0.65" of rain since last secchi reading on August 28.
Overcast.  Easterly wind about 5 mph.  About 1.8" of rain since last secchi reading on September 7.

Partly cloudy- wind SE 0-5 mph.  Lake will be lowered 1' in a week or so for dam repair.

Public perception also due to low water levels and lots of rain.  Clear- wind NW 5-10 mph.  Dam repair started 8/14.  Water level at low water mark.  About 9.7" of rain since 8/1 about 6.2" since ( ) .

Beautiful- sunny fall day. Slight southerly breeze. Assister by Judy Foster.
Assited by Judy Foster. Another beautiful fall day! The water is calm. We saw a bald eagle soaring over the lake. This is the final reading for this season. See you in the spring!
Assisted by Judy Foster Assisted by Judy Foster

Assisted by Judy Foster. Water is starting to turn brackish. Water appears to have a lot of suspended particulate in it. Last week the presence of Zebra Mussels was confirmed in Lake Morris by the DNR.
